{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312042734d6e5d227e6644f73","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"id":"20260312042734d6e5d227e6644f73","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Step 2: prizmkit.plan → plan.md"}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_e6eee94544c64ef2895c25f4","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:28:20.262Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"assistant","uuid":"20260312042734d6e5d227e6644f73","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"id":"20260312042734d6e5d227e6644f73","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde955ce415fd7c3d83e705ce70ae","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Implementation Plan\n\n## Architecture Overview\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                      Telegram Bot Entry                         │\n│                    src/bot/telegram.js                          │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Command Router                                │\n│              src/bot/commands/index.js                          │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │                 NEW: Permission Middleware               │   │\n│  │         src/security/permission-middleware.js            │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    Command Handlers                              │\n│     src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js                              │\n│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │            NEW: Confirmation Flow Handler                │   │\n│  │         src/bot/commands/confirmation.js                 │   │\n│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                 Security Layer (NEW)                             │\n│  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐                  │\n│  │ PermissionService │  │ ParameterSanitizer│                  │\n│  │ src/security/     │  │ src/security/     │                  │\n│  │ permission.js     │  │ sanitizer.js      │                  │\n│  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘                  │\n└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                        │\n                        ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                 Audit Service (NEW)                              │\n│              src/services/audit-service.js                      │\n│              logs/audit.log (JSON Lines)                        │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Component Design\n\n### C-1: PermissionService (`src/security/permission.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: 用户权限查询与管理\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- 解析 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 环境变量\n- 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` 查询接口\n- 提供 `hasPermission(userId, requiredLevel)` 校验接口\n- 权限级别比较逻辑\n\n**Dependencies**: `src/config.js`\n\n---\n\n### C-2: PermissionMiddleware (`src/security/permission-middleware.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: 命令级别的权限检查中间件\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- 读取命令元数据中的 `minPermission` 字段\n- 调用 `PermissionService` 校验用户权限\n- 返回统一错误响应或继续执行\n\n**Dependencies**: `src/security/permission.js`, `src/bot/commands/formatter.js`\n\n---\n\n### C-3: ParameterSanitizer (`src/security/sanitizer.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: 参数净化与校验\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- `sanitizePath(path)` - 路径净化\n- `sanitizeTargetId(id)` - 目标 ID 净化\n- `sanitizeGeneral(text)` - 通用文本净化\n- 危险字符检测与拒绝\n\n**Dependencies**: None\n\n---\n\n### C-4: ConfirmationFlow (`src/bot/commands/confirmation.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: 敏感操作二次确认流程\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- 生成确认请求消息\n- 管理待确认操作状态（内存 + 超时）\n- 校验确认响应（用户输入 \"CONFIRM\"）\n- 处理超时取消\n\n**Dependencies**: `src/security/permission.js`\n\n---\n\n### C-5: AuditService (`src/services/audit-service.js`)\n\n**Purpose**: 审计日志记录与查询\n\n**Responsibilities**:\n- 异步写入审计日志（JSON Lines）\n- 日志轮转管理\n- 按 userId/action/sessionId 查询\n- 敏感参数脱敏\n\n**Dependencies**: `src/config.js`\n\n---\n\n## Interface Design\n\n### I-1: PermissionService API\n\n```typescript\n// src/security/permission.js\n\nexport type PermissionLevel = 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer';\n\nexport interface PermissionConfig {\n  userPermissions: Map<string, PermissionLevel>;\n  defaultLevel: PermissionLevel;\n}\n\n/**\n * Get user's permission level.\n * @param userId - Telegram user ID\n * @returns Permission level (defaults to 'operator')\n */\nexport function getUserPermission(userId: string | number): PermissionLevel;\n\n/**\n * Check if user has required permission level.\n * @param userId - Telegram user ID\n * @param required - Required permission level\n * @returns True if user has sufficient permission\n */\nexport function hasPermission(userId: string | number, required: PermissionLevel): boolean;\n\n/**\n * Get the permission configuration.\n * @returns Permission config object\n */\nexport function getPermissionConfig(): PermissionConfig;\n```\n\n---\n\n### I-2: PermissionMiddleware API\n\n```typescript\n// src/security/permission-middleware.js\n\nexport interface CommandMeta {\n  name: string;\n  minPermission?: PermissionLevel; // NEW: required permission\n  requiresConfirmation?: boolean;   // NEW: requires confirmation flow\n  // ... existing fields\n}\n\n/**\n * Create permission check middleware.\n * @returns Middleware function for command router\n */\nexport function createPermissionMiddleware(): (ctx: Context, next: Next) => Promise<void>;\n\n/**\n * Check if command requires elevated permission.\n * @param commandName - Command name\n * @param meta - Command metadata\n * @returns Required permission level or null\n */\nexport function getRequiredPermission(commandName: string, meta: CommandMeta): PermissionLevel | null;\n```\n\n---\n\n### I-3: ParameterSanitizer API\n\n```typescript\n// src/security/sanitizer.js\n\nexport interface SanitizationResult {\n  ok: boolean;\n  value?: string;\n  error?: string;\n}\n\n// Dangerous characters to reject\nexport const DANGEROUS_CHARS = [';', '|', '&', '$', '`', \"'\", '\"', '(', ')', '<', '>', '..'];\n\n/**\n * Sanitize path parameter.\n * - Rejects path traversal (..)\n * - Rejects absolute paths outside allowed roots\n * - Rejects dangerous characters\n */\nexport function sanitizePath(input: string, allowedRoots?: string[]): SanitizationResult;\n\n/**\n * Sanitize target ID parameter.\n * - Only allows [A-Za-z0-9_-]+ pattern\n * - Max length 64 characters\n */\nexport function sanitizeTargetId(input: string): SanitizationResult;\n\n/**\n * Sanitize general text parameter.\n * - Rejects dangerous characters\n * - Trims whitespace\n */\nexport function sanitizeGeneral(input: string): SanitizationResult;\n\n/**\n * Check if input contains dangerous patterns.\n */\nexport function hasDangerousPatterns(input: string): boolean;\n```\n\n---\n\n### I-4: ConfirmationFlow API\n\n```typescript\n// src/bot/commands/confirmation.js\n\nexport interface PendingConfirmation {\n  id: string;\n  userId: string;\n  action: string;\n  params: Record<string, unknown>;\n  createdAt: Date;\n  expiresAt: Date;\n}\n\nexport interface ConfirmationResult {\n  confirmed: boolean;\n  expired: boolean;\n  cancelled: boolean;\n}\n\n/**\n * Request confirmation for a sensitive action.\n * @param ctx - Telegraf context\n * @param action - Action description\n * @param params - Action parameters\n * @param timeoutMs - Confirmation timeout (default 60000)\n * @returns Promise resolving to confirmation result\n */\nexport function requestConfirmation(\n  ctx: Context, \n  action: string, \n  params: Record<string, unknown>,\n  timeoutMs?: number\n): Promise<ConfirmationResult>;\n\n/**\n * Check if user has pending confirmation.\n */\nexport function hasPendingConfirmation(userId: string): boolean;\n\n/**\n * Cancel pending confirmation.\n */\nexport function cancelConfirmation(userId: string): void;\n\n/**\n * Handle confirmation response from user.\n */\nexport function handleConfirmationResponse(userId: string, response: string): ConfirmationResult | null;\n```\n\n---\n\n### I-5: AuditService API\n\n```typescript\n// src/services/audit-service.js\n\nexport interface AuditEntry {\n  timestamp: string;      // ISO 8601\n  userId: string;\n  username?: string;\n  action: string;\n  command?: string;\n  params: Record<string, unknown>;\n  result: 'success' | 'denied' | 'error';\n  errorMessage?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n}\n\nexport interface AuditQuery {\n  userId?: string;\n  action?: string;\n  sessionId?: string;\n  from?: Date;\n  to?: Date;\n  limit?: number;\n}\n\n/**\n * Log an audit entry.\n * @param entry - Audit entry to log\n */\nexport function logAudit(entry: AuditEntry): Promise<void>;\n\n/**\n * Query audit entries.\n * @param query - Query parameters\n * @returns Matching audit entries\n */\nexport function queryAudit(query: AuditQuery): Promise<AuditEntry[]>;\n\n/**\n * Get audit log path.\n */\nexport function getAuditLogPath(): string;\n\n/**\n * Perform log rotation if needed.\n */\nexport function rotateAuditLogIfNeeded(): Promise<void>;\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Model\n\n### D-1: Permission Configuration\n\n```javascript\n// Stored in memory, parsed from USER_PERMISSIONS env\n{\n  userPermissions: Map<string, PermissionLevel> {\n    '123456789' => 'admin',\n    '987654321' => 'operator',\n  },\n  defaultLevel: 'operator'\n}\n```\n\n### D-2: Command Metadata Extension\n\n```javascript\n// Extended in src/bot/commands/registry.js\n{\n  name: 'stop',\n  minPermission: 'admin',        // NEW\n  requiresConfirmation: true,    // NEW\n  // ... existing fields\n}\n```\n\n### D-3: Audit Log Entry (JSON Lines)\n\n```json\n{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"123456789\",\"username\":\"admin_user\",\"action\":\"stop\",\"command\":\"/stop\",\"params\":{\"type\":\"feature\"},\"result\":\"success\"}\n{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T10:31:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"987654321\",\"username\":\"operator_user\",\"action\":\"stop\",\"command\":\"/stop\",\"params\":{},\"result\":\"denied\",\"errorMessage\":\"Insufficient permission: requires admin, has operator\"}\n```\n\n### D-4: Pending Confirmation State\n\n```javascript\n// In-memory storage with TTL\nMap<string, PendingConfirmation> {\n  '987654321' => {\n    id: 'conf-abc123',\n    userId: '987654321',\n    action: 'stop',\n    params: { type: 'feature' },\n    createdAt: Date,\n    expiresAt: Date\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Module | Test File | Key Test Cases |\n|--------|-----------|----------------|\n| PermissionService | `tests/security/permission.test.js` | Permission parsing, level comparison, default behavior |\n| ParameterSanitizer | `tests/security/sanitizer.test.js` | Path traversal rejection, dangerous chars, valid inputs |\n| ConfirmationFlow | `tests/bot/confirmation.test.js` | Confirm/Cancel/Timeout flows, concurrent confirmations |\n| AuditService | `tests/services/audit-service.test.js` | Log writing, query, rotation, sanitization |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Test File | Description |\n|----------|-----------|-------------|\n| Permission Check Flow | `tests/integration/permission-flow.test.js` | End-to-end permission check in command routing |\n| Confirmation Flow | `tests/integration/confirmation-flow.test.js` | Full confirmation dialog interaction |\n| Audit Trail | `tests/integration/audit-trail.test.js` | Verify all sensitive actions are logged |\n\n### Test Coverage Target: > 90%\n\n---\n\n## Risk Assessment\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n| 权限配置错误导致管理员锁定 | Medium | High | 保留环境变量绕过机制，文档说明 |\n| 确认超时状态泄漏 | Low | Medium | 使用 WeakRef 或定时清理 |\n| 审计日志磁盘占满 | Low | Medium | 实施日志轮转和大小限制 |\n| 参数净化误杀合法输入 | Medium | Medium | 提供明确的错误提示，白名单模式 |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Phases\n\n### Phase 1: Core Security (T-010 ~ T-030)\n- Permission service\n- Permission middleware\n- Parameter sanitizer\n\n### Phase 2: Confirmation Flow (T-100 ~ T-120)\n- Confirmation handler\n- Integration with command handlers\n\n### Phase 3: Audit Logging (T-200 ~ T-220)\n- Audit service\n- Log rotation\n- Query API\n\n### Phase 4: Integration & Polish (T-900+)\n- Update all command handlers\n- Update registry metadata\n- Integration tests\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `src/security/permission.js` | CREATE | Permission service |\n| `src/security/permission-middleware.js` | CREATE | Permission middleware |\n| `src/security/sanitizer.js` | CREATE | Parameter sanitizer |\n| `src/bot/commands/confirmation.js` | CREATE | Confirmation flow |\n| `src/services/audit-service.js` | CREATE | Audit logging service |\n| `src/config.js` | MODIFY | Add permission/audit config |\n| `src/bot/commands/registry.js` | MODIFY | Add minPermission/requiresConfirmation fields |\n| `src/bot/commands/index.js` | MODIFY | Integrate permission middleware |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` | MODIFY | Add confirmation flow |\n| `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` | MODIFY | Add confirmation for reset |\n| `tests/security/*.test.js` | CREATE | Unit tests |\n| `tests/integration/*.test.js` | CREATE | Integration tests |\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/plan.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":35302,"output_tokens":3152,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_e6eee94544c64ef2895c25f4","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:28:20.268Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
