{"type":"assistant","uuid":"202603120428209d94a4dec50945d3","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"id":"202603120428209d94a4dec50945d3","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"019cde9610c67c2ad161b8e8adfaaf19","name":"Write","input":{"content":"# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Task List\n\n## Phase 0: Setup (T-001 ~ T-009)\n\n- [ ] [T-001] [P] Add permission config to src/config.js — file: src/config.js\n  - **Goal**: Add USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_DIR, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES config\n  - **Input**: Current config.js structure\n  - **Output**: Extended config with permission and audit settings\n  - **Acceptance**: Config parses USER_PERMISSIONS into Map, provides audit log defaults\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundational (T-010 ~ T-099)\n\n- [ ] [T-010] [P] Create PermissionService — file: src/security/permission.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement user permission query and comparison\n  - **Input**: Config with USER_PERMISSIONS\n  - **Output**: PermissionService with getUserPermission(), hasPermission(), getPermissionConfig()\n  - **Acceptance**: All functions work, default level is 'operator', permission comparison correct\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-011] [P] Create ParameterSanitizer — file: src/security/sanitizer.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement parameter sanitization utilities\n  - **Input**: Raw user input strings\n  - **Output**: SanitizationResult with ok/value/error\n  - **Acceptance**: sanitizePath rejects .. and absolute paths, sanitizeTargetId validates pattern, dangerous chars detected\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-012] Create PermissionMiddleware — file: src/security/permission-middleware.js\n  - **Goal**: Create middleware for command-level permission check\n  - **Input**: CommandMeta with minPermission, user context\n  - **Output**: Middleware function that checks permission before handler execution\n  - **Acceptance**: Blocks unauthorized users, allows authorized, returns proper error message\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-010\n\n- [ ] [T-013] [P] Create AuditService — file: src/services/audit-service.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement audit logging with JSON Lines format\n  - **Input**: AuditEntry objects\n  - **Output**: Written log entries, query API\n  - **Acceptance**: logAudit writes to file, queryAudit filters correctly, rotation works\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-014] Create ConfirmationFlow — file: src/bot/commands/confirmation.js\n  - **Goal**: Implement sensitive action confirmation mechanism\n  - **Input**: User context, action description, params\n  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog, pending state management, timeout handling\n  - **Acceptance**: requestConfirmation shows dialog, timeout cancels, CONFIRM response proceeds\n  - **Complexity**: High\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: User Stories (T-100 ~ T-899)\n\n### US-1: User Permission Levels\n\n- [ ] [T-100] Update command registry schema — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  - **Goal**: Add minPermission and requiresConfirmation to CommandMeta\n  - **Input**: Current registry.js\n  - **Output**: Extended CommandMeta type, updated registerCommand validation\n  - **Acceptance**: Commands can specify minPermission and requiresConfirmation\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **Depends on**: T-010\n\n### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n\n- [ ] [T-110] Integrate permission middleware into command router — file: src/bot/commands/index.js\n  - **Goal**: Add permission check to routeCommand flow\n  - **Input**: Current command router\n  - **Output**: Router checks permission before calling handler\n  - **Acceptance**: High-risk commands blocked for insufficient permission\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-012, T-100\n\n- [ ] [T-111] Add permission metadata to stop command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n  - **Goal**: Set stopMeta.minPermission = 'admin', requiresConfirmation = true\n  - **Input**: Current stop.js\n  - **Output**: Updated metadata\n  - **Acceptance**: stop command requires admin permission\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **Depends on**: T-100\n\n- [ ] [T-112] Add permission metadata to pipeline command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n  - **Goal**: Set appropriate minPermission for subcommands (reset = admin, retry = operator)\n  - **Input**: Current pipeline.js\n  - **Output**: Updated subcommand metadata\n  - **Acceptance**: reset requires admin, retry requires operator\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **Depends on**: T-100\n\n### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n\n- [ ] [T-120] Integrate sanitizer into command handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n  - **Goal**: Apply sanitizePath and sanitizeTargetId in all handlers that accept parameters\n  - **Input**: Handler params from parser\n  - **Output**: Sanitized params or error response\n  - **Acceptance**: Invalid params rejected with clear error message\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-011\n\n### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n\n- [ ] [T-130] Add confirmation flow to stop handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n  - **Goal**: Request confirmation before stopping pipeline (unless --force)\n  - **Input**: Current stop handler\n  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog before action\n  - **Acceptance**: stop shows confirmation, --force skips (admin only), timeout cancels\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-014, T-111\n\n- [ ] [T-131] Add confirmation flow to pipeline reset — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n  - **Goal**: Request confirmation before reset action\n  - **Input**: Current pipeline handler\n  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog before reset\n  - **Acceptance**: reset shows confirmation, --force skips (admin only)\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-014, T-112\n\n- [ ] [T-132] Handle confirmation response in message handler — file: src/bot/telegram.js\n  - **Goal**: Intercept user's CONFIRM response and process pending confirmation\n  - **Input**: User text message\n  - **Output**: Confirmation processed, action executed or cancelled\n  - **Acceptance**: \"CONFIRM\" triggers action, other messages show prompt\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-014\n\n### US-5: Audit Logging\n\n- [ ] [T-140] Add audit logging to command router — file: src/bot/commands/index.js\n  - **Goal**: Log all sensitive command executions (start, stop, reset, retry)\n  - **Input**: Command execution result\n  - **Output**: Audit log entry\n  - **Acceptance**: All sensitive actions logged with userId, action, params, result\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n  - **Depends on**: T-013\n\n- [ ] [T-141] Add audit log query command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n  - **Goal**: Create /audit command for querying audit logs (admin only)\n  - **Input**: Query params (userId, action, limit)\n  - **Output**: Formatted audit log entries\n  - **Acceptance**: Admin can query recent audit entries, non-admin denied\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  - **Depends on**: T-013\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Polish (T-900+)\n\n- [ ] [T-900] [P] Write unit tests for PermissionService — file: tests/security/permission.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for permission service\n  - **Input**: PermissionService module\n  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: All edge cases tested, permission levels verified\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-901] [P] Write unit tests for ParameterSanitizer — file: tests/security/sanitizer.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for sanitizer\n  - **Input**: ParameterSanitizer module\n  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: Path traversal, dangerous chars, valid inputs all tested\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-902] [P] Write unit tests for AuditService — file: tests/services/audit-service.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for audit service\n  - **Input**: AuditService module\n  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: Log writing, query, rotation all tested\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-903] Write unit tests for ConfirmationFlow — file: tests/bot/confirmation.test.js\n  - **Goal**: Test confirmation dialog, timeout, cancellation\n  - **Input**: ConfirmationFlow module\n  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n  - **Acceptance**: Confirm/cancel/timeout flows tested\n  - **Complexity**: Medium\n\n- [ ] [T-904] Write integration tests for permission flow — file: tests/integration/permission-flow.test.js\n  - **Goal**: End-to-end permission check in command routing\n  - **Input**: Mocked Telegraf context, command router\n  - **Output**: Integration test file\n  - **Acceptance**: Full permission flow from command to result tested\n  - **Complexity**: High\n\n- [ ] [T-905] Write integration tests for confirmation flow — file: tests/integration/confirmation-flow.test.js\n  - **Goal**: End-to-end confirmation dialog interaction\n  - **Input**: Mocked Telegraf context, confirmation module\n  - **Output**: Integration test file\n  - **Acceptance**: Full confirmation flow tested\n  - **Complexity**: High\n\n- [ ] [T-906] Update .env.example with new config — file: .env.example\n  - **Goal**: Document new configuration options\n  - **Input**: New config options\n  - **Output**: Updated .env.example\n  - **Acceptance**: USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_* documented\n  - **Complexity**: Low\n\n---\n\n## Dependency Graph\n\n```\nT-001 ──┬── T-010 ──┬── T-012 ──┬── T-110\n        │          │           │\n        │          └── T-100 ──┴── T-111, T-112\n        │\n        ├── T-011 ── T-120\n        │\n        └── T-013 ──┬── T-140\n                    │\n                    └── T-141\n\nT-014 ──┬── T-130\n        │\n        ├── T-131\n        │\n        └── T-132\n\nT-010, T-011, T-013, T-014 ── T-900, T-901, T-902, T-903\nT-110, T-130 ── T-904, T-905\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| Phase | Task Range | Count | Parallelizable |\n|-------|------------|-------|----------------|\n| Setup | T-001 | 1 | Yes |\n| Foundational | T-010~T-014 | 5 | Partial (T-010, T-011, T-013 parallel) |\n| User Stories | T-100~T-141 | 9 | Sequential within US groups |\n| Polish | T-900~T-906 | 7 | Partial (T-900~T-902 parallel) |\n\n**Total Tasks**: 22\n**Estimated Critical Path**: T-001 → T-010 → T-012 → T-110 → T-130 → T-904\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/tasks.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":38530,"output_tokens":2738,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_e6eee94544c64ef2895c25f4","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:29:02.339Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
