{"type":"user","uuid":"5b13527a-f826-4156-97a9-7b1f2b5b20fc","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde9790322e6bd07bf6146f962c93","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→---\n   2→name: prizm-dev-team-reviewer\n   3→description: PrizmKit-integrated quality reviewer. Uses prizmkit.analyze for cross-document consistency, prizmkit.code-review for spec compliance and code quality, and writes integration tests. Use when performing analysis, testing, or code review.\n   4→tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Glob, Grep, TaskCreate, TaskGet, TaskUpdate, TaskList, SendMessage\n   5→model: inherit\n   6→skills: prizmkit-code-review, prizmkit-analyze, prizmkit-prizm-docs\n   7→---\n   8→\n   9→你是 **Reviewer Agent**，PrizmKit-integrated Multi-Agent 软件开发协作团队的质量审查员。\n  10→\n  11→### 核心身份\n  12→\n  13→你是团队的\"质检员 + 校对员\"——不生产产品但确保质量，负责两个阶段的工作：\n  14→1. **交叉校验（Phase 4）**: 在实现前用 `prizmkit.analyze` 检查 spec/plan/tasks 的一致性\n  15→2. **评审（Phase 6）**: 在实现后用 `prizmkit.code-review` 检查代码质量，编写和执行集成测试\n  16→\n  17→### 项目上下文\n  18→\n  19→项目文档在 `.prizm-docs/`。审查前先读 `root.prizm` 了解项目规则（RULES）、模式（PATTERNS）和已知陷阱（TRAPS），需要时读取模块级文档。\n  20→\n  21→### 制品路径\n  22→\n  23→| 路径 | 用途 |\n  24→|------|------|\n  25→| `.prizm-docs/` | 项目知识层 — 规则、模式、已知陷阱 |\n  26→| `.prizmkit/specs/###-feature-name/` | 功能制品 — spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md |\n  27→\n  28→### 必须做 (MUST)\n  29→\n  30→1. Phase 4 时运行 `prizmkit.analyze` 做交叉一致性校验\n  31→2. Phase 6 时运行 `prizmkit.code-review` 做规格合规和代码质量审查\n  32→3. Phase 6 时编写和执行集成测试，验证模块间交互\n  33→4. 验证实际实现是否符合 plan.md 中的接口设计\n  34→5. 验证跨模块数据流的完整性和正确性\n  35→6. 测试边界条件和异常路径\n  36→7. 检查代码是否符合 `.prizm-docs/` RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  37→8. 审查是**只读操作**（Phase 4 和 Phase 6 的审查部分不修改代码文件）\n  38→9. 集成测试用例必须覆盖 spec.md 定义的所有用户故事\n  39→\n  40→### 绝不做 (NEVER)\n  41→\n  42→- 不编写实现代码（Dev 的职责）\n  43→- 不分解任务（PM 的职责）\n  44→- 不进行任务调度（Coordinator 的职责）\n  45→\n  46→### 行为规则\n  47→\n  48→```\n  49→REV-01: Phase 4 使用 prizmkit.analyze 做交叉校验\n  50→REV-02: Phase 6 使用 prizmkit.code-review 做代码审查\n  51→REV-03: 每个发现必须引用具体的文件路径和行号\n  52→REV-04: CRITICAL 级别发现必须包含具体的修复建议\n  53→REV-05: 最多 30 个发现（保持可操作性）\n  54→REV-06: Spec compliance 失败始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  55→REV-07: 安全发现始终为 HIGH 或 CRITICAL\n  56→REV-08: 集成测试必须覆盖 spec.md 所有用户故事\n  57→REV-09: 审查代码是否符合 .prizm-docs/ PATTERNS 和 RULES\n  58→```\n  59→\n  60→### Phase 4 工作流程：交叉校验\n  61→\n  62→**前置条件**: PM 已完成 spec.md / plan.md / tasks.md\n  63→\n  64→1. 运行 `prizmkit.analyze`（只读）\n  65→   - 输入: spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md\n  66→   - 6 个检测通道: 重复检测、歧义检测、不完整检测、Prizm 规则对齐、覆盖缺口、不一致性\n  67→   - 输出: 一致性分析报告（仅对话输出）\n  68→2. 如发现 CRITICAL 问题，报告给 Coordinator 退回 PM 修复\n  69→3. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含分析结果）\n  70→\n  71→### Phase 6 工作流程：评审\n  72→\n  73→**前置条件**: Dev 已完成实现，所有任务标记 `[x]`\n  74→\n  75→1. 读取 `.prizm-docs/root.prizm`，重点关注 RULES 和 PATTERNS\n  76→2. 运行 `prizmkit.code-review`（只读）\n  77→   - 6 个审查维度: 规格符合度、计划遵循度、代码质量、安全性、一致性、测试覆盖\n  78→   - 判定: PASS | PASS WITH WARNINGS | NEEDS FIXES\n  79→3. 编写和执行集成测试:\n  80→   - 接口合规性（请求格式、响应格式）\n  81→   - 跨模块数据流完整性\n  82→   - 用户故事验收标准（来自 spec.md）\n  83→   - 边界条件和异常路径\n  84→4. 生成统一评审报告\n  85→5. 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）\n  86→\n  87→### 判定标准\n  88→\n  89→| 判定 | 条件 | 后续动作 |\n  90→|------|------|---------|\n  91→| **PASS** | 无 CRITICAL 或 HIGH 发现 | 进入下一阶段 |\n  92→| **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS** | 无 CRITICAL，有 HIGH 发现 | 记录待改进项，可进入下一阶段 |\n  93→| **NEEDS_FIXES** | 存在 CRITICAL 发现 | 退回 Dev 修复后重新评审 |\n  94→\n  95→### 严重级别\n  96→\n  97→| 级别 | 定义 | 示例 |\n  98→|------|------|------|\n  99→| CRITICAL | 安全风险或严重架构问题 | SQL 注入、硬编码密钥 |\n 100→| HIGH | 影响可维护性的显著问题 | 规格不符、大量重复代码 |\n 101→| MEDIUM | 代码质量改进点 | 命名不统一、缺少注释 |\n 102→| LOW | 风格建议 | 格式微调、可选优化 |\n 103→\n 104→### 异常处理\n 105→\n 106→| 场景 | 策略 |\n 107→|------|------|\n 108→| analyze 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 PM 修复 |\n 109→| code-review 发现 CRITICAL | 报告 Coordinator → 退回 Dev 修复 |\n 110→| 集成测试失败 | 分类严重级别 → ISSUE_REPORT → Coordinator 派发给 Dev |\n 111→| 审查发现超过 30 个 | 只保留最严重的 30 个 |\n 112→| Prizm RULES 违规 | 自动标记为 CRITICAL |\n 113→\n 114→### 通信规则\n 115→\n 116→允许 Agent 之间直接通信，但关键消息和结论必须通知 Coordinator。\n 117→- 发送 COMPLETION_SIGNAL（含判定结果）标志完成\n 118→- 发送 ISSUE_REPORT 报告 CRITICAL 发现\n 119→- 接收 TASK_ASSIGNMENT 获取分配的工作\n 120→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6f94f3092aeb40b1a4cc64d7","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:30:03.298Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"fcddb862-006a-44d7-8429-db1855c66bc3","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde9792251cc6af49017d8bc6cc8d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L0\n   2→PROJECT_NAME: PrizmClaw\n   3→PROJECT_TYPE: telegram-bridge + web-api\n   4→ADOPTION_MODE: brownfield\n   5→PLATFORM: codebuddy\n   6→LANGUAGES: JavaScript(ESM), HTML, CSS, Python, Shell\n   7→PACKAGE_MANAGER: npm\n   8→ENTRYPOINTS: src/index.js -> src/http/server.js + src/bot/telegram.js\n   9→DOC_STATUS: initialized\n  10→ASSESSMENT: ASSESSMENT.md\n  11→MIGRATION_CANDIDATE: docs/AI_CONTEXT -> not_found\n  12→\n  13→MODULE_INDEX:\n  14→- runtime: src/** -> .prizm-docs/runtime.prizm\n  15→- web-ui: public/** -> .prizm-docs/web-ui.prizm\n  16→- pipeline: dev-pipeline/** -> .prizm-docs/pipeline.prizm\n  17→- dev-team: dev-team/** -> .prizm-docs/team.prizm\n  18→- project-config: package.json,.env.example,.codebuddy/settings.json,CODEBUDDY.md -> .prizm-docs/config.prizm\n  19→\n  20→LOAD_RULES:\n  21→- ON_SESSION_START: read .prizm-docs/root.prizm\n  22→- ON_TASK: load related L1 via MODULE_INDEX\n  23→- ON_EDIT: load/create related L2 lazily\n  24→\n  25→DEPENDENCY_HEALTH:\n  26→- outdated_major: dotenv,express,zod\n  27→- npm_audit_prod: 0 vulnerabilities\n  28→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6f94f3092aeb40b1a4cc64d7","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:30:03.299Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"25840ffe-056e-4720-8203-3da34c5edbfe","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde9793e4ec73e78adf771197e6f4","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard\n   2→\n   3→## Summary\n   4→\n   5→为 Telegram 管道控制增加安全护栏：用户权限分级、高风险命令授权校验、参数净化、敏感操作二次确认与审计日志。重点覆盖 stop/reset/retry/exec 等高风险指令，确保\"可用\"与\"可控\"并存。\n   6→\n   7→**Scope**: 权限分级模型、高风险命令拦截、参数净化、确认机制、审计日志。\n   8→\n   9→**Dependencies**: F-002 (Telegram Pipeline Command Router - completed), F-004 (Pipeline Process Controller - completed)\n  10→\n  11→---\n  12→\n  13→## User Stories\n  14→\n  15→### US-1: User Permission Levels\n  16→\n  17→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 基于用户 ID 的权限分级机制 **So that** 不同用户拥有不同的操作权限\n  18→\n  19→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  20→- AC-1.1: 支持三级权限: `admin` | `operator` | `viewer`\n  21→- AC-1.2: 通过环境变量 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 配置用户权限映射\n  22→- AC-1.3: 未配置时所有授权用户默认为 `operator`\n  23→- AC-1.4: 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` API 查询用户权限级别\n  24→\n  25→### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  26→\n  27→**As a** 系统管理员 **I want** 高风险命令需要特定权限级别才能执行 **So that** 敏感操作不会被未授权用户触发\n  28→\n  29→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  30→- AC-2.1: 定义高风险命令列表: `stop`, `reset`, `retry`, `exec`, `force-unlock`\n  31→- AC-2.2: `stop`/`reset`/`force-unlock` 需要 `admin` 权限\n  32→- AC-2.3: `retry` 需要 `operator` 权限\n  33→- AC-2.4: `exec` 需要 `admin` 权限且受 `ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC` 控制\n  34→- AC-2.5: 权限不足时返回统一拒绝消息，不暴露敏感信息\n  35→\n  36→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n  37→\n  38→**As a** 系统 **I want** 所有命令参数经过净化与规则校验 **So that** 非法路径与危险参数组合被拒绝\n  39→\n  40→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  41→- AC-3.1: 路径参数禁止 `..`、绝对路径穿越、shell 元字符\n  42→- AC-3.2: targetId 参数仅允许 `[A-Za-z0-9_-]+` 格式\n  43→- AC-3.3: 拒绝包含 `; | & $ \\` ' \" ( ) < >` 等危险字符的参数\n  44→- AC-3.4: 提供 `sanitizePath()` 和 `sanitizeTargetId()` 工具函数\n  45→\n  46→### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n  47→\n  48→**As a** 用户 **I want** 高风险命令执行前需要明确确认 **So that** 误操作可以被及时阻止\n  49→\n  50→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  51→- AC-4.1: `stop`、`reset`、`force-unlock` 需要二次确认\n  52→- AC-4.2: 确认消息包含操作摘要和风险提示\n  53→- AC-4.3: 用户需在 60 秒内回复确认，否则操作取消\n  54→- AC-4.4: 支持 `--force` 标志跳过确认（仅限 `admin` 用户）\n  55→\n  56→### US-5: Audit Logging\n  57→\n  58→**As a** 运维人员 **I want** 每次敏感操作都写入审计日志 **So that** 我可以追溯操作历史\n  59→\n  60→**Acceptance Criteria:**\n  61→- AC-5.1: 审计日志记录: timestamp, userId, username, action, params, result\n  62→- AC-5.2: 日志存储于 `logs/audit.log`（JSON Lines 格式）\n  63→- AC-5.3: 提供按会话 ID 或用户 ID 检索审计记录的 API\n  64→- AC-5.4: 日志轮转: 单文件最大 10MB，保留最近 5 个文件\n  65→\n  66→---\n  67→\n  68→## Non-Functional Requirements\n  69→\n  70→- **NFR-1 Performance**: 权限检查 < 5ms，参数净化 < 2ms，审计日志异步写入\n  71→- **NFR-2 Reliability**: 审计日志写入失败不影响命令执行，确认超时无死锁\n  72→- **NFR-3 Maintainability**: 权限配置与代码分离，高风险命令列表可配置，测试覆盖率 > 90%\n  73→- **NFR-4 Security**: 不在错误消息中暴露内部路径或配置，审计日志不可被普通用户访问\n  74→\n  75→---\n  76→\n  77→## Scope Boundaries\n  78→\n  79→**In Scope**: 用户权限分级模型与配置、高风险命令授权检查中间件、参数净化工具函数、确认对话机制、审计日志服务\n  80→\n  81→**Out of Scope**: 用户认证（已有 `isAllowedUser`）、Web UI 权限管理、数据库存储、加密存储\n  82→\n  83→---\n  84→\n  85→## High-Risk Command Matrix\n  86→\n  87→| Command | Min Permission | Confirmation | Notes |\n  88→|---------|---------------|--------------|-------|\n  89→| `stop` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 停止运行中管道 |\n  90→| `reset` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 重置管道状态 |\n  91→| `retry` | operator | No | 重试失败目标 |\n  92→| `exec` | admin | No | 执行系统命令 |\n  93→| `force-unlock` | admin | Yes (--force skips) | 强制释放锁 |\n  94→\n  95→---\n  96→\n  97→## Configuration\n  98→\n  99→```env\n 100→USER_PERMISSIONS=123456789:admin,987654321:operator\n 101→AUDIT_LOG_DIR=logs\n 102→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB=10\n 103→AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES=5\n 104→```\n 105→\n 106→---\n 107→\n 108→## Decisions\n 109→\n 110→| ID | Date | Decision |\n 111→|----|------|----------|\n 112→| D1 | 2026-03-12 | 使用三级权限模型（admin/operator/viewer）|\n 113→| D2 | 2026-03-12 | 确认机制使用文字确认（\"CONFIRM\"），不依赖 inline keyboard |\n 114→| D3 | 2026-03-12 | 审计日志使用 JSON Lines 格式 |\n 115→| D4 | 2026-03-12 | `--force` 标志仅限 admin 用户 |\n 116→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6f94f3092aeb40b1a4cc64d7","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:30:03.300Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"2902aab4-2989-4224-9763-e600b916abff","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde9795fd222e23c886f10a037ddc","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Implementation Plan\n   2→\n   3→## Architecture Overview\n   4→\n   5→```\n   6→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n   7→│                      Telegram Bot Entry                         │\n   8→│                    src/bot/telegram.js                          │\n   9→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  10→                        │\n  11→                        ▼\n  12→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  13→│                    Command Router                                │\n  14→│              src/bot/commands/index.js                          │\n  15→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  16→│  │                 NEW: Permission Middleware               │   │\n  17→│  │         src/security/permission-middleware.js            │   │\n  18→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  19→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  20→                        │\n  21→                        ▼\n  22→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  23→│                    Command Handlers                              │\n  24→│     src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js                              │\n  25→│  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐   │\n  26→│  │            NEW: Confirmation Flow Handler                │   │\n  27→│  │         src/bot/commands/confirmation.js                 │   │\n  28→│  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘   │\n  29→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  30→                        │\n  31→                        ▼\n  32→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  33→│                 Security Layer (NEW)                             │\n  34→│  ┌───────────────────┐  ┌───────────────────┐                  │\n  35→│  │ PermissionService │  │ ParameterSanitizer│                  │\n  36→│  │ src/security/     │  │ src/security/     │                  │\n  37→│  │ permission.js     │  │ sanitizer.js      │                  │\n  38→│  └───────────────────┘  └───────────────────┘                  │\n  39→└───────────────────────┬─────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  40→                        │\n  41→                        ▼\n  42→┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n  43→│                 Audit Service (NEW)                              │\n  44→│              src/services/audit-service.js                      │\n  45→│              logs/audit.log (JSON Lines)                        │\n  46→└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n  47→```\n  48→\n  49→---\n  50→\n  51→## Component Design\n  52→\n  53→### C-1: PermissionService (`src/security/permission.js`)\n  54→\n  55→**Purpose**: 用户权限查询与管理\n  56→\n  57→**Responsibilities**:\n  58→- 解析 `USER_PERMISSIONS` 环境变量\n  59→- 提供 `getUserPermission(userId)` 查询接口\n  60→- 提供 `hasPermission(userId, requiredLevel)` 校验接口\n  61→- 权限级别比较逻辑\n  62→\n  63→**Dependencies**: `src/config.js`\n  64→\n  65→---\n  66→\n  67→### C-2: PermissionMiddleware (`src/security/permission-middleware.js`)\n  68→\n  69→**Purpose**: 命令级别的权限检查中间件\n  70→\n  71→**Responsibilities**:\n  72→- 读取命令元数据中的 `minPermission` 字段\n  73→- 调用 `PermissionService` 校验用户权限\n  74→- 返回统一错误响应或继续执行\n  75→\n  76→**Dependencies**: `src/security/permission.js`, `src/bot/commands/formatter.js`\n  77→\n  78→---\n  79→\n  80→### C-3: ParameterSanitizer (`src/security/sanitizer.js`)\n  81→\n  82→**Purpose**: 参数净化与校验\n  83→\n  84→**Responsibilities**:\n  85→- `sanitizePath(path)` - 路径净化\n  86→- `sanitizeTargetId(id)` - 目标 ID 净化\n  87→- `sanitizeGeneral(text)` - 通用文本净化\n  88→- 危险字符检测与拒绝\n  89→\n  90→**Dependencies**: None\n  91→\n  92→---\n  93→\n  94→### C-4: ConfirmationFlow (`src/bot/commands/confirmation.js`)\n  95→\n  96→**Purpose**: 敏感操作二次确认流程\n  97→\n  98→**Responsibilities**:\n  99→- 生成确认请求消息\n 100→- 管理待确认操作状态（内存 + 超时）\n 101→- 校验确认响应（用户输入 \"CONFIRM\"）\n 102→- 处理超时取消\n 103→\n 104→**Dependencies**: `src/security/permission.js`\n 105→\n 106→---\n 107→\n 108→### C-5: AuditService (`src/services/audit-service.js`)\n 109→\n 110→**Purpose**: 审计日志记录与查询\n 111→\n 112→**Responsibilities**:\n 113→- 异步写入审计日志（JSON Lines）\n 114→- 日志轮转管理\n 115→- 按 userId/action/sessionId 查询\n 116→- 敏感参数脱敏\n 117→\n 118→**Dependencies**: `src/config.js`\n 119→\n 120→---\n 121→\n 122→## Interface Design\n 123→\n 124→### I-1: PermissionService API\n 125→\n 126→```typescript\n 127→// src/security/permission.js\n 128→\n 129→export type PermissionLevel = 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer';\n 130→\n 131→export interface PermissionConfig {\n 132→  userPermissions: Map<string, PermissionLevel>;\n 133→  defaultLevel: PermissionLevel;\n 134→}\n 135→\n 136→/**\n 137→ * Get user's permission level.\n 138→ * @param userId - Telegram user ID\n 139→ * @returns Permission level (defaults to 'operator')\n 140→ */\n 141→export function getUserPermission(userId: string | number): PermissionLevel;\n 142→\n 143→/**\n 144→ * Check if user has required permission level.\n 145→ * @param userId - Telegram user ID\n 146→ * @param required - Required permission level\n 147→ * @returns True if user has sufficient permission\n 148→ */\n 149→export function hasPermission(userId: string | number, required: PermissionLevel): boolean;\n 150→\n 151→/**\n 152→ * Get the permission configuration.\n 153→ * @returns Permission config object\n 154→ */\n 155→export function getPermissionConfig(): PermissionConfig;\n 156→```\n 157→\n 158→---\n 159→\n 160→### I-2: PermissionMiddleware API\n 161→\n 162→```typescript\n 163→// src/security/permission-middleware.js\n 164→\n 165→export interface CommandMeta {\n 166→  name: string;\n 167→  minPermission?: PermissionLevel; // NEW: required permission\n 168→  requiresConfirmation?: boolean;   // NEW: requires confirmation flow\n 169→  // ... existing fields\n 170→}\n 171→\n 172→/**\n 173→ * Create permission check middleware.\n 174→ * @returns Middleware function for command router\n 175→ */\n 176→export function createPermissionMiddleware(): (ctx: Context, next: Next) => Promise<void>;\n 177→\n 178→/**\n 179→ * Check if command requires elevated permission.\n 180→ * @param commandName - Command name\n 181→ * @param meta - Command metadata\n 182→ * @returns Required permission level or null\n 183→ */\n 184→export function getRequiredPermission(commandName: string, meta: CommandMeta): PermissionLevel | null;\n 185→```\n 186→\n 187→---\n 188→\n 189→### I-3: ParameterSanitizer API\n 190→\n 191→```typescript\n 192→// src/security/sanitizer.js\n 193→\n 194→export interface SanitizationResult {\n 195→  ok: boolean;\n 196→  value?: string;\n 197→  error?: string;\n 198→}\n 199→\n 200→// Dangerous characters to reject\n 201→export const DANGEROUS_CHARS = [';', '|', '&', '$', '`', \"'\", '\"', '(', ')', '<', '>', '..'];\n 202→\n 203→/**\n 204→ * Sanitize path parameter.\n 205→ * - Rejects path traversal (..)\n 206→ * - Rejects absolute paths outside allowed roots\n 207→ * - Rejects dangerous characters\n 208→ */\n 209→export function sanitizePath(input: string, allowedRoots?: string[]): SanitizationResult;\n 210→\n 211→/**\n 212→ * Sanitize target ID parameter.\n 213→ * - Only allows [A-Za-z0-9_-]+ pattern\n 214→ * - Max length 64 characters\n 215→ */\n 216→export function sanitizeTargetId(input: string): SanitizationResult;\n 217→\n 218→/**\n 219→ * Sanitize general text parameter.\n 220→ * - Rejects dangerous characters\n 221→ * - Trims whitespace\n 222→ */\n 223→export function sanitizeGeneral(input: string): SanitizationResult;\n 224→\n 225→/**\n 226→ * Check if input contains dangerous patterns.\n 227→ */\n 228→export function hasDangerousPatterns(input: string): boolean;\n 229→```\n 230→\n 231→---\n 232→\n 233→### I-4: ConfirmationFlow API\n 234→\n 235→```typescript\n 236→// src/bot/commands/confirmation.js\n 237→\n 238→export interface PendingConfirmation {\n 239→  id: string;\n 240→  userId: string;\n 241→  action: string;\n 242→  params: Record<string, unknown>;\n 243→  createdAt: Date;\n 244→  expiresAt: Date;\n 245→}\n 246→\n 247→export interface ConfirmationResult {\n 248→  confirmed: boolean;\n 249→  expired: boolean;\n 250→  cancelled: boolean;\n 251→}\n 252→\n 253→/**\n 254→ * Request confirmation for a sensitive action.\n 255→ * @param ctx - Telegraf context\n 256→ * @param action - Action description\n 257→ * @param params - Action parameters\n 258→ * @param timeoutMs - Confirmation timeout (default 60000)\n 259→ * @returns Promise resolving to confirmation result\n 260→ */\n 261→export function requestConfirmation(\n 262→  ctx: Context, \n 263→  action: string, \n 264→  params: Record<string, unknown>,\n 265→  timeoutMs?: number\n 266→): Promise<ConfirmationResult>;\n 267→\n 268→/**\n 269→ * Check if user has pending confirmation.\n 270→ */\n 271→export function hasPendingConfirmation(userId: string): boolean;\n 272→\n 273→/**\n 274→ * Cancel pending confirmation.\n 275→ */\n 276→export function cancelConfirmation(userId: string): void;\n 277→\n 278→/**\n 279→ * Handle confirmation response from user.\n 280→ */\n 281→export function handleConfirmationResponse(userId: string, response: string): ConfirmationResult | null;\n 282→```\n 283→\n 284→---\n 285→\n 286→### I-5: AuditService API\n 287→\n 288→```typescript\n 289→// src/services/audit-service.js\n 290→\n 291→export interface AuditEntry {\n 292→  timestamp: string;      // ISO 8601\n 293→  userId: string;\n 294→  username?: string;\n 295→  action: string;\n 296→  command?: string;\n 297→  params: Record<string, unknown>;\n 298→  result: 'success' | 'denied' | 'error';\n 299→  errorMessage?: string;\n 300→  sessionId?: string;\n 301→}\n 302→\n 303→export interface AuditQuery {\n 304→  userId?: string;\n 305→  action?: string;\n 306→  sessionId?: string;\n 307→  from?: Date;\n 308→  to?: Date;\n 309→  limit?: number;\n 310→}\n 311→\n 312→/**\n 313→ * Log an audit entry.\n 314→ * @param entry - Audit entry to log\n 315→ */\n 316→export function logAudit(entry: AuditEntry): Promise<void>;\n 317→\n 318→/**\n 319→ * Query audit entries.\n 320→ * @param query - Query parameters\n 321→ * @returns Matching audit entries\n 322→ */\n 323→export function queryAudit(query: AuditQuery): Promise<AuditEntry[]>;\n 324→\n 325→/**\n 326→ * Get audit log path.\n 327→ */\n 328→export function getAuditLogPath(): string;\n 329→\n 330→/**\n 331→ * Perform log rotation if needed.\n 332→ */\n 333→export function rotateAuditLogIfNeeded(): Promise<void>;\n 334→```\n 335→\n 336→---\n 337→\n 338→## Data Model\n 339→\n 340→### D-1: Permission Configuration\n 341→\n 342→```javascript\n 343→// Stored in memory, parsed from USER_PERMISSIONS env\n 344→{\n 345→  userPermissions: Map<string, PermissionLevel> {\n 346→    '123456789' => 'admin',\n 347→    '987654321' => 'operator',\n 348→  },\n 349→  defaultLevel: 'operator'\n 350→}\n 351→```\n 352→\n 353→### D-2: Command Metadata Extension\n 354→\n 355→```javascript\n 356→// Extended in src/bot/commands/registry.js\n 357→{\n 358→  name: 'stop',\n 359→  minPermission: 'admin',        // NEW\n 360→  requiresConfirmation: true,    // NEW\n 361→  // ... existing fields\n 362→}\n 363→```\n 364→\n 365→### D-3: Audit Log Entry (JSON Lines)\n 366→\n 367→```json\n 368→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T10:30:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"123456789\",\"username\":\"admin_user\",\"action\":\"stop\",\"command\":\"/stop\",\"params\":{\"type\":\"feature\"},\"result\":\"success\"}\n 369→{\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-12T10:31:00.000Z\",\"userId\":\"987654321\",\"username\":\"operator_user\",\"action\":\"stop\",\"command\":\"/stop\",\"params\":{},\"result\":\"denied\",\"errorMessage\":\"Insufficient permission: requires admin, has operator\"}\n 370→```\n 371→\n 372→### D-4: Pending Confirmation State\n 373→\n 374→```javascript\n 375→// In-memory storage with TTL\n 376→Map<string, PendingConfirmation> {\n 377→  '987654321' => {\n 378→    id: 'conf-abc123',\n 379→    userId: '987654321',\n 380→    action: 'stop',\n 381→    params: { type: 'feature' },\n 382→    createdAt: Date,\n 383→    expiresAt: Date\n 384→  }\n 385→}\n 386→```\n 387→\n 388→---\n 389→\n 390→## Testing Strategy\n 391→\n 392→### Unit Tests\n 393→\n 394→| Module | Test File | Key Test Cases |\n 395→|--------|-----------|----------------|\n 396→| PermissionService | `tests/security/permission.test.js` | Permission parsing, level comparison, default behavior |\n 397→| ParameterSanitizer | `tests/security/sanitizer.test.js` | Path traversal rejection, dangerous chars, valid inputs |\n 398→| ConfirmationFlow | `tests/bot/confirmation.test.js` | Confirm/Cancel/Timeout flows, concurrent confirmations |\n 399→| AuditService | `tests/services/audit-service.test.js` | Log writing, query, rotation, sanitization |\n 400→\n 401→### Integration Tests\n 402→\n 403→| Scenario | Test File | Description |\n 404→|----------|-----------|-------------|\n 405→| Permission Check Flow | `tests/integration/permission-flow.test.js` | End-to-end permission check in command routing |\n 406→| Confirmation Flow | `tests/integration/confirmation-flow.test.js` | Full confirmation dialog interaction |\n 407→| Audit Trail | `tests/integration/audit-trail.test.js` | Verify all sensitive actions are logged |\n 408→\n 409→### Test Coverage Target: > 90%\n 410→\n 411→---\n 412→\n 413→## Risk Assessment\n 414→\n 415→| Risk | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n 416→|------|-------------|--------|------------|\n 417→| 权限配置错误导致管理员锁定 | Medium | High | 保留环境变量绕过机制，文档说明 |\n 418→| 确认超时状态泄漏 | Low | Medium | 使用 WeakRef 或定时清理 |\n 419→| 审计日志磁盘占满 | Low | Medium | 实施日志轮转和大小限制 |\n 420→| 参数净化误杀合法输入 | Medium | Medium | 提供明确的错误提示，白名单模式 |\n 421→\n 422→---\n 423→\n 424→## Implementation Phases\n 425→\n 426→### Phase 1: Core Security (T-010 ~ T-030)\n 427→- Permission service\n 428→- Permission middleware\n 429→- Parameter sanitizer\n 430→\n 431→### Phase 2: Confirmation Flow (T-100 ~ T-120)\n 432→- Confirmation handler\n 433→- Integration with command handlers\n 434→\n 435→### Phase 3: Audit Logging (T-200 ~ T-220)\n 436→- Audit service\n 437→- Log rotation\n 438→- Query API\n 439→\n 440→### Phase 4: Integration & Polish (T-900+)\n 441→- Update all command handlers\n 442→- Update registry metadata\n 443→- Integration tests\n 444→\n 445→---\n 446→\n 447→## File Changes Summary\n 448→\n 449→| File | Action | Description |\n 450→|------|--------|-------------|\n 451→| `src/security/permission.js` | CREATE | Permission service |\n 452→| `src/security/permission-middleware.js` | CREATE | Permission middleware |\n 453→| `src/security/sanitizer.js` | CREATE | Parameter sanitizer |\n 454→| `src/bot/commands/confirmation.js` | CREATE | Confirmation flow |\n 455→| `src/services/audit-service.js` | CREATE | Audit logging service |\n 456→| `src/config.js` | MODIFY | Add permission/audit config |\n 457→| `src/bot/commands/registry.js` | MODIFY | Add minPermission/requiresConfirmation fields |\n 458→| `src/bot/commands/index.js` | MODIFY | Integrate permission middleware |\n 459→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` | MODIFY | Add confirmation flow |\n 460→| `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` | MODIFY | Add confirmation for reset |\n 461→| `tests/security/*.test.js` | CREATE | Unit tests |\n 462→| `tests/integration/*.test.js` | CREATE | Integration tests |\n 463→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6f94f3092aeb40b1a4cc64d7","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:30:03.300Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"d0991719-ee00-4860-94fd-b2e24a0a48c6","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"019cde97980138932d662bce96295f31","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→# F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Task List\n   2→\n   3→## Phase 0: Setup (T-001 ~ T-009)\n   4→\n   5→- [ ] [T-001] [P] Add permission config to src/config.js — file: src/config.js\n   6→  - **Goal**: Add USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_DIR, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_SIZE_MB, AUDIT_LOG_MAX_FILES config\n   7→  - **Input**: Current config.js structure\n   8→  - **Output**: Extended config with permission and audit settings\n   9→  - **Acceptance**: Config parses USER_PERMISSIONS into Map, provides audit log defaults\n  10→  - **Complexity**: Low\n  11→\n  12→---\n  13→\n  14→## Phase 1: Foundational (T-010 ~ T-099)\n  15→\n  16→- [ ] [T-010] [P] Create PermissionService — file: src/security/permission.js\n  17→  - **Goal**: Implement user permission query and comparison\n  18→  - **Input**: Config with USER_PERMISSIONS\n  19→  - **Output**: PermissionService with getUserPermission(), hasPermission(), getPermissionConfig()\n  20→  - **Acceptance**: All functions work, default level is 'operator', permission comparison correct\n  21→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  22→\n  23→- [ ] [T-011] [P] Create ParameterSanitizer — file: src/security/sanitizer.js\n  24→  - **Goal**: Implement parameter sanitization utilities\n  25→  - **Input**: Raw user input strings\n  26→  - **Output**: SanitizationResult with ok/value/error\n  27→  - **Acceptance**: sanitizePath rejects .. and absolute paths, sanitizeTargetId validates pattern, dangerous chars detected\n  28→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  29→\n  30→- [ ] [T-012] Create PermissionMiddleware — file: src/security/permission-middleware.js\n  31→  - **Goal**: Create middleware for command-level permission check\n  32→  - **Input**: CommandMeta with minPermission, user context\n  33→  - **Output**: Middleware function that checks permission before handler execution\n  34→  - **Acceptance**: Blocks unauthorized users, allows authorized, returns proper error message\n  35→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  36→  - **Depends on**: T-010\n  37→\n  38→- [ ] [T-013] [P] Create AuditService — file: src/services/audit-service.js\n  39→  - **Goal**: Implement audit logging with JSON Lines format\n  40→  - **Input**: AuditEntry objects\n  41→  - **Output**: Written log entries, query API\n  42→  - **Acceptance**: logAudit writes to file, queryAudit filters correctly, rotation works\n  43→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  44→\n  45→- [ ] [T-014] Create ConfirmationFlow — file: src/bot/commands/confirmation.js\n  46→  - **Goal**: Implement sensitive action confirmation mechanism\n  47→  - **Input**: User context, action description, params\n  48→  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog, pending state management, timeout handling\n  49→  - **Acceptance**: requestConfirmation shows dialog, timeout cancels, CONFIRM response proceeds\n  50→  - **Complexity**: High\n  51→\n  52→---\n  53→\n  54→## Phase 2: User Stories (T-100 ~ T-899)\n  55→\n  56→### US-1: User Permission Levels\n  57→\n  58→- [ ] [T-100] Update command registry schema — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  59→  - **Goal**: Add minPermission and requiresConfirmation to CommandMeta\n  60→  - **Input**: Current registry.js\n  61→  - **Output**: Extended CommandMeta type, updated registerCommand validation\n  62→  - **Acceptance**: Commands can specify minPermission and requiresConfirmation\n  63→  - **Complexity**: Low\n  64→  - **Depends on**: T-010\n  65→\n  66→### US-2: High-Risk Command Authorization\n  67→\n  68→- [ ] [T-110] Integrate permission middleware into command router — file: src/bot/commands/index.js\n  69→  - **Goal**: Add permission check to routeCommand flow\n  70→  - **Input**: Current command router\n  71→  - **Output**: Router checks permission before calling handler\n  72→  - **Acceptance**: High-risk commands blocked for insufficient permission\n  73→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n  74→  - **Depends on**: T-012, T-100\n  75→\n  76→- [ ] [T-111] Add permission metadata to stop command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n  77→  - **Goal**: Set stopMeta.minPermission = 'admin', requiresConfirmation = true\n  78→  - **Input**: Current stop.js\n  79→  - **Output**: Updated metadata\n  80→  - **Acceptance**: stop command requires admin permission\n  81→  - **Complexity**: Low\n  82→  - **Depends on**: T-100\n  83→\n  84→- [ ] [T-112] Add permission metadata to pipeline command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n  85→  - **Goal**: Set appropriate minPermission for subcommands (reset = admin, retry = operator)\n  86→  - **Input**: Current pipeline.js\n  87→  - **Output**: Updated subcommand metadata\n  88→  - **Acceptance**: reset requires admin, retry requires operator\n  89→  - **Complexity**: Low\n  90→  - **Depends on**: T-100\n  91→\n  92→### US-3: Parameter Sanitization\n  93→\n  94→- [ ] [T-120] Integrate sanitizer into command handlers — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/*.js\n  95→  - **Goal**: Apply sanitizePath and sanitizeTargetId in all handlers that accept parameters\n  96→  - **Input**: Handler params from parser\n  97→  - **Output**: Sanitized params or error response\n  98→  - **Acceptance**: Invalid params rejected with clear error message\n  99→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 100→  - **Depends on**: T-011\n 101→\n 102→### US-4: Confirmation for Sensitive Actions\n 103→\n 104→- [ ] [T-130] Add confirmation flow to stop handler — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js\n 105→  - **Goal**: Request confirmation before stopping pipeline (unless --force)\n 106→  - **Input**: Current stop handler\n 107→  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog before action\n 108→  - **Acceptance**: stop shows confirmation, --force skips (admin only), timeout cancels\n 109→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 110→  - **Depends on**: T-014, T-111\n 111→\n 112→- [ ] [T-131] Add confirmation flow to pipeline reset — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js\n 113→  - **Goal**: Request confirmation before reset action\n 114→  - **Input**: Current pipeline handler\n 115→  - **Output**: Confirmation dialog before reset\n 116→  - **Acceptance**: reset shows confirmation, --force skips (admin only)\n 117→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 118→  - **Depends on**: T-014, T-112\n 119→\n 120→- [ ] [T-132] Handle confirmation response in message handler — file: src/bot/telegram.js\n 121→  - **Goal**: Intercept user's CONFIRM response and process pending confirmation\n 122→  - **Input**: User text message\n 123→  - **Output**: Confirmation processed, action executed or cancelled\n 124→  - **Acceptance**: \"CONFIRM\" triggers action, other messages show prompt\n 125→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 126→  - **Depends on**: T-014\n 127→\n 128→### US-5: Audit Logging\n 129→\n 130→- [ ] [T-140] Add audit logging to command router — file: src/bot/commands/index.js\n 131→  - **Goal**: Log all sensitive command executions (start, stop, reset, retry)\n 132→  - **Input**: Command execution result\n 133→  - **Output**: Audit log entry\n 134→  - **Acceptance**: All sensitive actions logged with userId, action, params, result\n 135→  - **Complexity**: Low\n 136→  - **Depends on**: T-013\n 137→\n 138→- [ ] [T-141] Add audit log query command — file: src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n 139→  - **Goal**: Create /audit command for querying audit logs (admin only)\n 140→  - **Input**: Query params (userId, action, limit)\n 141→  - **Output**: Formatted audit log entries\n 142→  - **Acceptance**: Admin can query recent audit entries, non-admin denied\n 143→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 144→  - **Depends on**: T-013\n 145→\n 146→---\n 147→\n 148→## Phase 3: Polish (T-900+)\n 149→\n 150→- [ ] [T-900] [P] Write unit tests for PermissionService — file: tests/security/permission.test.js\n 151→  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for permission service\n 152→  - **Input**: PermissionService module\n 153→  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n 154→  - **Acceptance**: All edge cases tested, permission levels verified\n 155→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 156→\n 157→- [ ] [T-901] [P] Write unit tests for ParameterSanitizer — file: tests/security/sanitizer.test.js\n 158→  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for sanitizer\n 159→  - **Input**: ParameterSanitizer module\n 160→  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n 161→  - **Acceptance**: Path traversal, dangerous chars, valid inputs all tested\n 162→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 163→\n 164→- [ ] [T-902] [P] Write unit tests for AuditService — file: tests/services/audit-service.test.js\n 165→  - **Goal**: Comprehensive test coverage for audit service\n 166→  - **Input**: AuditService module\n 167→  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n 168→  - **Acceptance**: Log writing, query, rotation all tested\n 169→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 170→\n 171→- [ ] [T-903] Write unit tests for ConfirmationFlow — file: tests/bot/confirmation.test.js\n 172→  - **Goal**: Test confirmation dialog, timeout, cancellation\n 173→  - **Input**: ConfirmationFlow module\n 174→  - **Output**: Test file with >90% coverage\n 175→  - **Acceptance**: Confirm/cancel/timeout flows tested\n 176→  - **Complexity**: Medium\n 177→\n 178→- [ ] [T-904] Write integration tests for permission flow — file: tests/integration/permission-flow.test.js\n 179→  - **Goal**: End-to-end permission check in command routing\n 180→  - **Input**: Mocked Telegraf context, command router\n 181→  - **Output**: Integration test file\n 182→  - **Acceptance**: Full permission flow from command to result tested\n 183→  - **Complexity**: High\n 184→\n 185→- [ ] [T-905] Write integration tests for confirmation flow — file: tests/integration/confirmation-flow.test.js\n 186→  - **Goal**: End-to-end confirmation dialog interaction\n 187→  - **Input**: Mocked Telegraf context, confirmation module\n 188→  - **Output**: Integration test file\n 189→  - **Acceptance**: Full confirmation flow tested\n 190→  - **Complexity**: High\n 191→\n 192→- [ ] [T-906] Update .env.example with new config — file: .env.example\n 193→  - **Goal**: Document new configuration options\n 194→  - **Input**: New config options\n 195→  - **Output**: Updated .env.example\n 196→  - **Acceptance**: USER_PERMISSIONS, AUDIT_LOG_* documented\n 197→  - **Complexity**: Low\n 198→\n 199→---\n 200→\n 201→## Dependency Graph\n 202→\n 203→```\n 204→T-001 ──┬── T-010 ──┬── T-012 ──┬── T-110\n 205→        │          │           │\n 206→        │          └── T-100 ──┴── T-111, T-112\n 207→        │\n 208→        ├── T-011 ── T-120\n 209→        │\n 210→        └── T-013 ──┬── T-140\n 211→                    │\n 212→                    └── T-141\n 213→\n 214→T-014 ──┬── T-130\n 215→        │\n 216→        ├── T-131\n 217→        │\n 218→        └── T-132\n 219→\n 220→T-010, T-011, T-013, T-014 ── T-900, T-901, T-902, T-903\n 221→T-110, T-130 ── T-904, T-905\n 222→```\n 223→\n 224→---\n 225→\n 226→## Summary\n 227→\n 228→| Phase | Task Range | Count | Parallelizable |\n 229→|-------|------------|-------|----------------|\n 230→| Setup | T-001 | 1 | Yes |\n 231→| Foundational | T-010~T-014 | 5 | Partial (T-010, T-011, T-013 parallel) |\n 232→| User Stories | T-100~T-141 | 9 | Sequential within US groups |\n 233→| Polish | T-900~T-906 | 7 | Partial (T-900~T-902 parallel) |\n 234→\n 235→**Total Tasks**: 22\n 236→**Estimated Critical Path**: T-001 → T-010 → T-012 → T-110 → T-130 → T-904\n 237→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_6f94f3092aeb40b1a4cc64d7","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:30:03.301Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
