tization behavior\n  41→  - Input: Various dangerous and safe inputs\n  42→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  43→  - Acceptance: Path traversal, shell injection, length limits tested\n  44→  - Complexity: Low\n  45→  - Depends: T-012\n  46→\n  47→### Confirmation Manager Module\n  48→\n  49→- [x] [T-014] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` core logic — file: src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n  50→  - Goal: Manage confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  51→  - Input: userId, action, params, timeout\n  52→  - Output: confirmId, status, action confirmation\n  53→  - Acceptance: Create/confirm/expire/cancel flows work\n  54→  - Complexity: Medium\n  55→\n  56→- [x] [T-015] Implement `confirmation-manager.js` unit tests — file: tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js\n  57→  - Goal: Verify confirmation lifecycle\n  58→  - Input: Various confirmation scenarios\n  59→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  60→  - Acceptance: Timeout, cancel, double-confirm tested\n  61→  - Complexity: Low\n  62→  - Depends: T-014\n  63→\n  64→### Audit Log Service\n  65→\n  66→- [x] [T-016] Implement `audit-log-service.js` core logic — file: src/services/audit-log-service.js\n  67→  - Goal: Write and query audit logs\n  68→  - Input: Audit entries, query filters\n  69→  - Output: JSON Lines log files\n  70→  - Acceptance: Async write, query by user/time/action\n  71→  - Complexity: Medium\n  72→\n  73→- [x] [T-017] Implement `audit-log-service.js` unit tests — file: tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js\n  74→  - Goal: Verify logging behavior\n  75→  - Input: Log entries, query parameters\n  76→  - Output: Test coverage > 90%\n  77→  - Acceptance: Write, query, rotation tested\n  78→  - Complexity: Low\n  79→  - Depends: T-016\n  80→\n  81→---\n  82→\n  83→## Phase 3: User Stories (T-100+)\n  84→\n  85→### US-1: Permission Tiers\n  86→\n  87→- [x] [T-101] [US-1] Integrate permission guard into command registry — file: src/bot/commands/registry.js\n  88→  - Goal: Add permission che