| HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS: stop, reset, force-unlock |\n| AC-4.2 | ✅ PASS | Confirmation message includes action and params - confirmation-manager.js:55 |\n| AC-4.3 | ✅ PASS | DEFAULT_TIMEOUT_MS = 60000 - confirmation-manager.js:14 |\n| AC-4.4 | ✅ PASS | --force flag bypass for admin - stop.js:62-63, pipeline.js:240-241 |\n\n### US-5: Audit Logging\n\n| AC | Status | Evidence |\n|----|--------|----------|\n| AC-5.1 | ✅ PASS | All fields logged - audit-log-service.js:174-183 |\n| AC-5.2 | ✅ PASS | JSON Lines format - audit-log-service.js:186 |\n| AC-5.3 | ✅ PASS | `queryAuditLogs()` API with filters |\n| AC-5.4 | ✅ PASS | Rotation with maxFiles - audit-log-service.js:124-146 |\n\n---\n\n## 2. NFR Compliance\n\n| NFR | Status | Evidence |\n|-----|--------|----------|\n| NFR-1 Performance | ✅ PASS | Tests confirm < 5ms for permission, < 2ms for sanitization |\n| NFR-2 Reliability | ✅ PASS | Audit write failures logged but don't block - audit-log-service.js:194 |\n| NFR-3 Maintainability | ✅ PASS | Config separated, test coverage > 90% |\n| NFR-4 Security | ✅ PASS | No sensitive info in error messages |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Findings\n\n### HIGH Severity\n\n**None**\n\n### MEDIUM Severity\n\n| ID | File | Line | Finding | Recommendation |\n|----|------|------|---------|----------------|\n| M-01 | param-sanitizer.js | 101-116 | `isPath` option logic has dead code path - the filter always returns all patterns since `!p.includes('path traversal')` is always falsy | Remove or fix the path-specific logic |\n| M-02 | stop.js | 19 | Local `pendingConfirmations` Map is separate from confirmation-manager's internal Map | Consider using the centralized confirmation manager storage |\n| M-03 | pipeline.js | 26 | Same as M-02 - local pending confirmations duplicating state | Consider using centralized storage |\n\n### LOW Severity\n\n| ID | File | Line | Finding | Recommendation |\n|----|------|------|---------|----------------|\n| L-01 | permission-guard.js | 44 | `_config` variable could be `config` reference causing test pollution | Already handled by setConfigForTesting/resetConfig - minor cleanup possible |\n| L-02 | audit-log-service.js | 189-191 | Comment mentions async write could be added but implementation is already async | Update comment for clarity |\n| L-03 | confirmation-manager.js | 55 | Hardcoded \"60 秒\" in message instead of using timeoutMs parameter | Use dynamic timeout in message |\n\n---\n\n## 4. Security Review\n\n| Check | Status | Notes |\n|-------|--------|-------|\n| No hardcoded secrets | ✅ PASS | All config from env vars |\n| Input validation | ✅ PASS | All params sanitized |\n| Path traversal prevention | ✅ PASS | `..` blocked in validatePath |\n| Shell injection prevention | ✅ PASS | Dangerous chars blocked |\n| Error message security | ✅ PASS | No sensitive info exposed |\n| Defense in depth | ✅ PASS | Double-check in audit.js:60 |\n\n---\n\n## 5. Test Coverage\n\n| Module | Coverage | Notes |\n|--------|----------|-------|\n| permission-guard.js | ✅ > 90% | All role/command combos tested |\n| param-sanitizer.js | ✅ > 90% | All dangerous patterns tested |\n| confirmation-manager.js | ✅ > 90% | Full lifecycle tested |\n| audit-log-service.js | ✅ > 90% | Write, query, rotation tested |\n| Integration | ✅ Covered | Full security flow tested |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Integration Test Results\n\nAll existing tests pass with exit code 0.\n\n**Tests executed**:\n- tests/security/permission-guard.test.js (25 tests)\n- tests/security/param-sanitizer.test.js (27 tests)\n- tests/security/confirmation-manager.test.js (18 tests)\n- tests/services/audit-log-service.test.js (18 tests)\n- tests/integration/security-flow.test.js (13 tests)\n\n---\n\n## 7. Recommendations\n\n### Must Fix (for future iterations)\nNone - all acceptance criteria met.\n\n### Should Consider\n1. **M-01**: Fix the dead code path in `isPath` logic\n2. **M-02/M-03**: Centralize pending confirmations storage\n3. Add unit tests for the `/audit` command handler\n\n### Nice to Have\n1. Add configurable timeout message\n2. Add metrics/monitoring for permission denials\n3. Consider rate limiting for failed permission checks\n\n---\n\n## 8. Verdict\n\n**PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n**Rationale**:\n- All 22 acceptance criteria met\n- No CRITICAL or HIGH severity findings\n- 3 MEDIUM severity findings (code quality, not security)\n- Test coverage > 90%\n- All NFR requirements met\n- Security requirements satisfied\n\nThe implementation correctly implements the safety and permission guard feature as specified. The MEDIUM findings are code quality improvements that don't affect functionality or security.\n\n**Next Steps**:\n1. Consider fixing M-01 to M-03 in a follow-up task\n2. Feature can proceed to deployment\n","file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/006-safety-and-permission-guard/review-report.md"}}],"model":"glm-5.0","role":"assistant","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":69110,"output_tokens":1780,"cache_creation_input_tokens":null,"cache_read_input_tokens":null,"cache_creation":null,"server_tool_use":null,"service_tier":null}},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_0d027c03943d4ecf95a6fbf8","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:51:03.396Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
