lear suggestions\n  75→- US-7: Authorization guard on all commands\n  76→\n  77→### Commands Implemented\n  78→\n  79→| Command | Aliases | Description |\n  80→|---------|---------|-------------|\n  81→| `/pipeline` | `/p` | Manage pipelines (run/status/logs/stop) |\n  82→| `/bugfix` | `/b` | Start bugfix pipeline |\n  83→| `/planner` | — | Manage planner pipelines |\n  84→| `/status` | `/s` | Show running pipelines |\n  85→| `/logs` | `/l` | View pipeline logs |\n  86→| `/stop` | — | Stop running pipelines |\n  87→\n  88→### Verification\n  89→\n  90→- `npm test`: 105 tests pass (76 for F-002)\n  91→- Code review: PASS\n  92→- All 21 tasks completed\n  93→\n  94→---\n  95→\n  96→## F-003: Feature and Bug Plan Ingestion\n  97→\n  98→**Status:** completed  \n  99→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 100→\n 101→### Deliverables\n 102→\n 103→- `src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js` - Schema validation, version management, plan registry\n 104→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js` - Plan command handler (status/versions/use/rollback/validate)\n 105→- `src/bot/telegram.js` - Document upload handler for JSON files\n 106→- `src/services/pipeline-control-service.js` - Extended with resolvePlanListPath()\n 107→- `src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js` - Extended with plansDir config\n 108→- `plans/` directory structure with feature-list/ and bug-fix-list/ subdirectories\n 109→- Unit tests in `tests/services/plan-ingestion-service.test.js`\n 110→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f003-plan-ingestion.integration.test.js`\n 111→\n 112→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 113→\n 114→- US-1: Upload Plan File - Telegram document message handling with auto-type detection\n 115→- US-2: Schema Validation - Ajv-based validation with field-level error messages\n 116→- US-3: Version Management - Timestamp-based versioning with use/rollback commands\n 117→- US-4: Plan Status Query - Status command showing version info and content summary\n 118→- US-5: Plan Integrity Protection - Validation precedes save, current version preserved on error\n 119→- US-6: Pipeline Integration - resolvePlanListPath() for dynamic plan path resolution\n 120→\n 121→### Commands Implemented\n 122→\n 123→| Command | Subcommands | Description |\n 124→|---------|-------------|-------------|\n 125→| `/plan` | status, versions, use, rollback, validate | Manage plan files |\n 126→\n 127→### Verification\n 128→\n 129→- Code review: PASS_WITH_WARNINGS\n 130→- All 18 tasks completed\n 131→- Unit tests: 19 passing\n 132→- Integration tests: 10 passing\n 133→\n 134→---\n 135→\n 136→## F-004: Pipeline Process Controller\n 137→\n 138→**Status:** completed\n 139→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-12\n 140→\n 141→### Deliverables\n 142→\n 143→- `src/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.js` - File-based lock management with PID validation\n 144→- `src/pipeline-infra/state-manager.js` - State file reading/writing for daemon and pipeline state\n 145→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 6 new error codes for F-004\n 146→- `src/pipeline-infra/path-policy.js` - Extended with lock/state path resolvers\n 147→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Unified pipeline control API with concurrency protection\n 148→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/pipeline.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 149→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 150→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 151→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/stop.js` - Updated to use pipeline-controller\n 152→- Unit tests in `tests/pipeline-infra/lock-manager.test.js` and `tests/pipeline-infra/state-manager.test.js`\n 153→- Unit tests in `tests/services/pipeline-controller.test.js`\n 154→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f004-pipeline-controller.integration.test.js`\n 155→\n 156→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 157→\n 158→- US-1: Unified Pipeline Start - startPipeline with daemon/foreground modes, lock acquisition\n 159→- US-2: Pipeline Stop - stopPipeline with ALREADY_STOPPED handling, lock release\n 160→- US-3: Target Retry - retryTarget with validation and mode support\n 161→- US-4: Run Single Feature - runSingle without lock (independent execution)\n 162→- US-5: Status Query - getStatus with daemon/pipeline state, lastResult\n 163→- US-6: Logs Query - getLogs with line limit, missing file handling\n 164→- US-7: Concurrency Protection - lock-manager with stale lock cleanup, forceUnlock\n 165→- US-8: Error Mapping - Consistent error codes with hint/context fields\n 166→- US-9: Telegram Handler Integration - All handlers updated to use pipeline-controller\n 167→\n 168→### Error Codes Added\n 169→\n 170→| Code | Description |\n 171→|------|-------------|\n 172→| LOCK_ACQUISITION_FAILED | Pipeline already running |\n 173→| ALREADY_STOPPED | Pipeline not running |\n 174→| PIPELINE_NOT_RUNNING | No active pipeline |\n 175→| INVALID_TARGET | Missing or invalid target ID |\n 176→| TARGET_NOT_RETRYABLE | Target state not retryable |\n 177→| DAEMON_START_FAILED | Failed to start daemon |\n 178→\n 179→### Key Decisions\n 180→\n 181→- D1: File lock + PID validation for concurrency protection (no external dependencies)\n 182→- D2: Separate lock-manager module for single responsibility\n 183→- D3: Reuse existing state files (backward compatible)\n 184→- D4: New pipeline-controller module vs extending pipeline-control-service\n 185→- D5: runSingle does NOT acquire lock (independent execution)\n 186→\n 187→### Verification\n 188→\n 189→- Code review: PASS\n 190→- 128 of 143 tasks completed (core functionality complete)\n 191→- Unit tests: 80+ passing\n 192→- Integration tests: 20+ passing\n 193→\n 194→---\n 195→\n 196→## F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n 197→\n 198→**Status:** completed\n 199→**Completion Date:** 2026-03-13\n 200→\n 201→### Deliverables\n 202→\n 203→- `src/services/status-aggregator.js` - Aggregates state from multiple sources for unified status view\n 204→- `src/services/log-pager.js` - Paginated log reading with streaming support for large files\n 205→- `src/services/telegram-pusher.js` - Telegram message pushing with throttling, chunking, heartbeat\n 206→- `src/services/index.js` - Exports all new services\n 207→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/status.js` - Updated with aggregated status and --type parameter\n 208→- `src/bot/commands/handlers/logs.js` - Updated with pagination (--lines, --offset, --file)\n 209→- `src/pipeline-infra/error-codes.js` - Extended with 8 new error codes for F-005\n 210→- `src/services/pipeline-controller.js` - Extended with lifecycle hooks (on/off/emit)\n 211→- Unit tests in `tests/services/status-aggregator.test.js`, `tests/services/log-pager.test.js`, `tests/services/telegram-pusher.test.js`\n 212→- Integration tests in `tests/integration/f005-status-and-logs.integration.test.js`\n 213→\n 214→### Acceptance Criteria Met\n 215→\n 216→- US-1: Aggregated Status Query - /status shows running/paused/completed/failed/idle state with progress\n 217→- US-2: Paginated Logs Query - /logs with --lines, --offset, --type parameters (max 500 lines)\n 218→- US-3: Message Length Compliance - Auto-chunking at 4000 chars with [N/M] segment numbering\n 219→- US-4: Heartbeat Progress Push - Event-driven heartbeat with 30s throttle\n 220→- US-5: Error Summary Push - Error notifications with log lines and duration\n 221→- US-6: Diagnostic Error Messages - Friendly messages for missing/corrupted state files\n 222→\n 223→### Commands Enhanced\n 224→\n 225→| Command | New Parameters | Description |\n 226→|---------|----------------|-------------|\n 227→| `/status` | `--type=feature\\|bugfix` | Aggregated pipeline status |\n 228→| `/logs` | `--lines=N --offset=N --type=feature\\|bugfix --file` | Paginated log viewing |\n 229→\n 230→### Error Codes Added\n 231→\n 232→| Code | Description |\n 233→|------|-------------|\n 234→| STATE_FILE_MISSING | State file not found |\n 235→| STATE_FILE_CORRUPTED | JSON parse error |\n 236→| LOG_FILE_MISSING | Log file not found |\n 237→| LOG_READ_ERROR | Log read failure |\n 238→| SEND_FAILED | Telegram send failure |\n 239→| FILE_SEND_FAILED | File send failure |\n 240→| HEARTBEAT_DISABLED | Heartbeat not enabled |\n 241→| INVALID_PIPELINE_TYPE | Invalid pipeline type |\n 242→\n 243→### Key Decisions\n 244→\n 245→- D1: Independent status-aggregator service (single responsibility)\n 246→- D2: In-memory message queue with retry (non-blocking)\n 247→- D3: CLI argument pagination (simple, no complex protocol)\n 248→- D4: Event-driven heartbeat + time throttle (30s minimum interval)\n 249→- D5: Real-time error extraction from logs (no additional storage)\n 250→- D6: Lifecycle hooks via EventEmitter in pipeline-controller\n 251→- D7: Message retry: max 3, exponential backoff (1s → 2s → 4s)\n 252→\n 253→### Verification\n 254→\n 255→- All 77 tasks completed\n 256→- Unit tests: 120+ passing\n 257→- Integration tests: 15+ passing\n 258→- NFR-1: Status aggregation < 200ms, log read < 300ms\n 259→- NFR-2: Push failures don't block pipeline (queue + retry)\n 260→- NFR-3: Test coverage > 85%\n 261→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_eae735c497af42f4877ad667","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:53:38.341Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
