{"type":"user","uuid":"8bbfbe66-5600-47e4-8977-c2d87d7724a3","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_465cfd3e32134ace9848e95a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L2\n   2→MODULE: security\n   3→PATH: src/security/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: Security guard layer for permission tiers, param sanitization, and confirmation flow\n   5→\n   6→KEY_FILES:\n   7→- src/security/index.js -> module exports\n   8→- src/security/permission-guard.js -> role hierarchy and command authorization\n   9→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js -> parameter sanitization and dangerous pattern detection\n  10→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js -> confirmation flow for high-risk actions\n  11→- src/security/guard.js -> existing user authorization\n  12→- src/security/system-guard.js -> system exec authorization\n  13→\n  14→INTERFACES:\n  15→- getUserRole(userId) -> 'admin' | 'operator' | 'viewer'\n  16→- checkCommandPermission(userId, command) -> { allowed, requiresConfirmation, reason }\n  17→- isAdmin(userId) -> boolean\n  18→- sanitizeParam(input, options) -> { ok, value?, error? }\n  19→- validatePath(path, allowedRoots) -> { ok, resolved?, error? }\n  20→- detectDangerousPatterns(input) -> { safe, patterns }\n  21→- createConfirmation(userId, action, params, timeoutMs) -> { confirmId, message }\n  22→- checkConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> { status, action?, params? }\n  23→- confirmAction(confirmId, userId) -> { ok, action?, params?, error? }\n  24→- cancelConfirmation(confirmId, userId) -> void\n  25→- logAuditEntry(entry) -> Promise<void>\n  26→- queryAuditLogs(filters) -> Promise<Object[]>\n  27→\n  28→ROLE_HIERARCHY:\n  29→- viewer: 0 -> can view status and logs\n  30→- operator: 1 -> can run pipelines and retry\n  31→- admin: 2 -> can stop, reset, force-unlock, exec\n  32→\n  33→COMMAND_PERMISSIONS:\n  34→- status, logs: viewer\n  35→- pipeline, bugfix, planner, retry: operator\n  36→- stop, reset, force-unlock, exec: admin\n  37→\n  38→HIGH_RISK_COMMANDS:\n  39→- stop, reset, force-unlock -> require confirmation (CONFIRM text)\n  40→- admin can skip confirmation with --force flag\n  41→\n  42→DANGEROUS_PATTERNS:\n  43→- path traversal (..)\n  44→- shell injection (backticks, $(), ${})\n  45→- command chains (||, &&, ;)\n  46→- home directory expansion (~)\n  47→- exec/eval flags\n  48→\n  49→AUDIT_LOG:\n  50→- format: JSON Lines (.jsonl)\n  51→- fields: timestamp, userId, role, action, params, result, reason, sessionId\n  52→- rotation: max 10MB per file, max 5 files\n  53→\n  54→TRAPS:\n  55→- unknown users default to 'operator' role\n  56→- permission denied is logged before returning error\n  57→- confirmation expires after 60 seconds\n  58→- audit log write failures are silent (non-blocking)\n  59→- param sanitizer rejects all dangerous patterns regardless of context\n  60→\n  61→DEPENDS_ON:\n  62→- src/config.js -> USER_PERMISSIONS, ALLOW_ADMIN_SKIP_CONFIRM, AUDIT_LOG_*\n  63→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_465cfd3e32134ace9848e95a","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:54:31.442Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
{"type":"user","uuid":"73a30968-cdf7-4653-bc6f-03183df9e9d7","session_id":"531490f3-af15-4b63-b1c5-2c677e54409f","message":{"content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_74a90efbf56c4552917e7d5d","content":[{"type":"text","text":"   1→DOC_LEVEL: L1\n   2→MODULE: runtime\n   3→PATH: src/**\n   4→DESCRIPTION: telegram + web request handling + sessioned CodeBuddy bridge\n   5→\n   6→ENTRYPOINT:\n   7→- src/index.js -> createHttpServer + optional Telegram bot launch\n   8→\n   9→KEY_FILES:\n  10→- src/config.js\n  11→- src/http/server.js\n  12→- src/routes/api-routes.js\n  13→- src/services/chat-service.js\n  14→- src/services/pipeline-control-service.js\n  15→- src/services/plan-ingestion-service.js\n  16→- src/services/audit-log-service.js\n  17→- src/pipeline-infra/config-loader.js\n  18→- src/pipeline-infra/script-runner.js\n  19→- src/adapters/codebuddy.js\n  20→- src/bot/telegram.js\n  21→- src/bot/commands/handlers/plan.js\n  22→- src/bot/commands/handlers/audit.js\n  23→- src/security/permission-guard.js\n  24→- src/security/param-sanitizer.js\n  25→- src/security/confirmation-manager.js\n  26→- src/services/system-exec-service.js\n  27→\n  28→SUBDIRS:\n  29→- src/adapters -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/adapters.prizm\n  30→- src/bot -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/bot.prizm\n  31→- src/http -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/http.prizm\n  32→- src/routes -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/routes.prizm\n  33→- src/security -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/security.prizm\n  34→- src/services -> .prizm-docs/runtime/services.prizm\n  35→- src/pipeline-infra -> .prizm-docs/runtime/pipeline-infra.prizm\n  36→- src/utils -> (lazy) .prizm-docs/runtime/utils.prizm\n  37→\n  38→INTERFACES:\n  39→- HTTP: /healthz, /api/events(SSE), /api/chat, /api/chat/reset, /api/screenshot, /api/system/exec\n  40→- Telegram: /start, /help, /reset, /screenshot, /exec, /pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop, /plan, /audit, text message relay\n  41→- Security: PermissionGuard, ParamSanitizer, ConfirmationManager, AuditLogService\n  42→\n  43→TRAPS:\n  44→- ENABLE_TELEGRAM=true requires TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\n  45→- system exec is disabled unless ENABLE_SYSTEM_EXEC=true\n  46→- system exec requires ALLOWED_COMMAND_PREFIXES whitelist\n  47→- chat is serialized per session via chat-queue\n  48→- high-risk commands (stop, reset, force-unlock) require admin role and confirmation\n  49→- permission check happens before command handler execution\n  50→- param sanitizer blocks path traversal and shell injection patterns\n  51→- audit logs are async written, failure does not block execution\n  52→\n  53→DECISIONS:\n  54→- 2026-03-09 | runtime-doc-init | model first-pass runtime map from source + API surface\n  55→- 2026-03-10 | runtime-infra-f001 | expose pipeline infra config in src/config.js and pipeline-control-service API for feature/bugfix run/status/stop/retry/logs/reset\n  56→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f002 | add command routing layer for pipeline commands (/pipeline, /bugfix, /planner, /status, /logs, /stop)\n  57→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f003 | add plan ingestion service for feature-list/bug-fix-list upload, validation, version management, and /plan command\n  58→- 2026-03-12 | runtime-f006 | add security guard layer with permission tiers, param sanitization, confirmation flow, and audit logging\n  59→"}],"is_error":false}],"role":"user"},"parent_tool_use_id":"call_74a90efbf56c4552917e7d5d","__timestamp":"2026-03-11T20:54:31.443Z","_requestId":"1836a01aa07b4323b33253678e844458"}
